 to those concerned with the origins of Indian and American thought, activism, and poetry.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aPhilosophy in literature. 0aSpirituality in literature. 4aAmerican Studies : American Studies. 4aAsian Studies : India and South Asian Studies. 4aLiterature : American Literature. 4aLiterature : Comparative Literature. 4aLiterature : Literature. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aRELIGION / Hinduism / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978079147747240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791477472423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791477472/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles